data.title: Royal Netherlands Air Force bases and units
data.meta_description: Military airfields and Royal Netherlands Air Force units are dispersed throughout the Netherlands. The Air Force also has units stationed with other Dutch Defence elements and abroad.
data.text:
Aircraft and helicopters

The F-16s of the Royal Netherlands Air Force are stationed at the Leeuwarden and Volkel air bases, while Eindhoven is the home of the Air Forceâ€™s transport aircraft. Gilze-Rijen Air Base is the main hub of the Defence Helicopter Command, which also has elements based at De Kooy Naval Air Station and Deelen Military Aviation Facility.
